  "texts": [
    "To achieve this, we use DeBERTa-V3 (He et al., 2021) as a representative of masked language models (Devlin et al., 2019) and fine-tune it on the GLUE benchmark (Wang et al., 2019).",
    "We repeat the experiment with four seeds and report the evaluation results in Table 5 with the standard deviation in the subscript.",
    "Comparing PoLAR with LoRA, we note significant improvements across all tasks except for QQP and MRPC where results are comparable.",
    "These results highlight that PoLAR can handle both autoregressive as well as masked language model setups.",
    "For X ∈ R m×r, a landing step requires O(m 2 r) FLOPs while a retraction-based routine only requires O(mr 2) operations."
